I'm a regular viewer and deeply respect the work you do to expose political narratives.

I'm messaging to raise something serious: there's a quiet but dangerous shift happening  the replacement of Ashoka Stambh with the Sengol, especially in Parliament and now in Maharashtra Loksabha passes, where Ashokas emblem has reportedly been removed.

This isnt just symbolic. It feels like an attempt to erase Buddha, Ashoka, and even Babasaheb's constitutional values  and replace them with rituals and monarchy-based symbols like Sengol.

Why is Ashoka being erased from official spaces? Who benefits from this?

Can your team please investigate this narrative? Its flying under the radar  but if ignored, this could be the start of a much more dangerous transformation.

Many of us look to you to bring these buried truths to light. Hope you'll dig into this.
